# .understandignore — aggressive scope for vLLM's core architecture
# Goal: focus on the v1 engine, entrypoints, config, distributed scheduler,
# and model_executor base classes. Exclude the long tail of repetitive
# model/layer/kernel implementations and vendored dependencies.
#
# Syntax: same as .gitignore (globs, # comments, ! negation, trailing / for dirs)
# Built-in defaults already exclude: node_modules/, .git/, dist/, build/, *.lock,
# *.min.js, etc.

